content.value: At Blankets for T.O., we are supporting a petition in order to give more vaccination priority to the homeless of Toronto. Read more about the cause and join the petition by clicking below. Spread the message to friends and family!
As Blankets for T.O. looks back on 2020, read up on the initiatives we completed in 2020 and the milestones we reached by reading our 2020 Annual Report.
Listen to podcasts associated with BTO, covering everything from homeless issues to university life to the latest advancements in medicine and technology. More information coming soon.

node.title: Water.org UTSC x BTO Winter/Holiday Event

childMarkdownRemark.html: We collaborate with Water.org UTSC to provide students with opportunities to socialize with friends, win prizes in games and raffles, and become better informed about homelessness in Toronto and water scarcity around the world.
In November 2020, still amid the COVID-19 Pandemic, BTO engaged in a donut distribution initiative while also helping to promote a local small business on campus.
In October, Blankets for T.O. hosted a pumpkin carving contest for UTSC students and giveaway.

childContentfulOrganizationInformationOr.organizationFrontBlurb: Blankets for T.O. is a non-profit organization situated at the University of Toronto that strives to provide support and resources to those in need within the city of Toronto, as well as raise awareness on the ongoing stigma surrounding homelessness, with the ultimate goal of eradicating it. So far, our team has worked towards our goal by distributing food blankets, and masks to those in need, as well as hand sanitizers due to the ongoing pandemic. We have also interviewed and shared the experiences through our social media presences of those who support the less fortunate, in the hopes of educating others on the severity of homelessness in Toronto, and encouraging them to support the people in their community.
